Package org.hms.services.drugdispensary

Class DrugReplenishRequestTable

java.lang.Object
org.hms.entities.AbstractTable<DrugReplenishRequest>
org.hms.services.drugdispensary.DrugReplenishRequestTable
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class DrugReplenishRequestTable extends AbstractTable<DrugReplenishRequest>
Represents a table for managing and storing drug replenish requests. Provides functionality to handle entries, headers, and file operations associated with drug replenish requests.

  • Field Details

    • HEADERS

      private static final String[] HEADERS
      Represents the headers for the Drug Replenish Request table. These headers correspond to the fields of the drug replenish request entries.

    • formatString

      private static final String formatString
      Format string used to define the structure of the ASCII table rows. The format follows the pattern: "│ %-4s│ %-15s│ %-5s│ %-60s│\n" The placeholders represent: - ID (4 characters wide) - Drug Name (15 characters wide) - Quantity to Add (5 characters wide) - Notes (60 characters wide)
      See Also:
      • Constant Field Values

  • Constructor Details

    • DrugReplenishRequestTable

      public DrugReplenishRequestTable()
      This constructor creates a new DrugReplenishRequestTable without linking to a file. Calls to saveToFile() will have no effect. Calling saveToFile(String filePath) will NOT link the table to a file too. To link to a file, either use the constructor that takes a filePath parameter. Or call setFilePath(String filePath).

    • DrugReplenishRequestTable

      public DrugReplenishRequestTable(String filePath)

      Parameters:
      filePath - the path of the file to link with this table.

      public String toPrintString()
